news.title: Bengaluru civic body identifies two lakh illegal buildings, numbers may go up
news.para: BBMP special commissioner (projects) Ravindra PN has said the Palike has identified 16,086 buildings which have deviated from their sanctioned plans and 1,81,236 buildings which have come up on B khata properties.

news.title: Noida: 15 more farmhouses on Yamuna banks razed, owners to pay demolition cost
news.para: In a public notice, Noida CEO Ritu Maheshwari said that construction work cannot be carried out in the notified area of the Authority without prior permission.

news.title: Gurugram: Over 400 families in Ansal Versalia await proper power connection
news.para: The residents alleged that the developer kept the homebuyers in the dark about the electricity connection before possession despite collecting all the required funds for the same, and “now threatens to snap power supply from diesel generators if anyone raises the issue”.

news.title: NCLT directs investigation against Wave Megacity for alleged siphoning of buyers' money
news.para: ​Evidence has been produced by the homebuyers that Wave Megacity was taking huge amount of cash from them but has failed to either give them possession of flats or return the money, observed a two-member bench of NCLT.

news.title: Sunac China seeks to extend $345 million onshore bond repayments by two years: Sources
news.para: Sunac plans to pay only the interest on the maturity date on Monday, while repaying the 2.3 billion yuan ($345 million) debt in four instalments of 10%, 15%, 20% and 55% of the principal through June 13, 2024.

news.title: DDA opens 90-day window for receiving more applications for land pooling
news.para: A new window of 90 days has been opened, starting late May, for people to apply under the land pooling policy. Also, this period is to also allow setting up of a consortium for three sectors under the policy," he said.

news.title: PNB board okays Rs 500 crore infusion in PNB Housing Finance
news.para: The public sector bank board has approved the bank's participation in the proposed rights issue for an amount up to 500 crore in order to retain the bank's shareholding in the mortgage lender at 30% or below but above 26%.

news.title: Kochi: Smart city projects lagging, many of them yet to take off
news.para: According to project officials, the deadline for completing the projects undertaken by the CSML has been extended to July 2023. Some projects are yet to even commence.

news.title: Canara Bank, Karur Vysya raise lending rates
news.para: State-owned Canara Bank has raised the marginal cost of funds based lending rate (MCLR) by 0.05 per cent of 5 basis points to 7.40 per cent for one year tenure.

news.title: Sand bank auction delay hits construction sector in Jharkhand
news.para: The Hemant Soren government told the members of the Jharkhand Vidhan Sabha in March that only 22 out of the 608 sand banks were functional while the auctioning for the rest would be completed within a fortnight.

news.title: An old-money billionaire rises up against Gautam Adani
news.para: Kumar Mangalam Birla comes from old money, unlike Adani, a first-generation entrepreneur. His great-grandfather, who diversified from textile trading to jute manufacturing and a lot else besides, was a confidante of Mahatma Gandhi’s during India’s freedom struggle.

news.title: About 80% of Gandhinagar residential plots don't have parking
news.para: They were allotted plots at subsidized rates or were sold plots of 50, 71, 81, 90, 135, 200, 250, or 330 square metres. The capital’s town planners thought of wide roads, balancing concrete with greenery, laying down well-defined commercial and residential areas, and a well-connected road network.

news.title: Mumbai: Govandi housing society residents want fume-emitting concrete plant relocated
news.para: In a letter to the municipal ward officer sent last week the residents have said that the particulate emissions from the plant are degrading the air quality apart from it residents have to put up with constant noise pollution throughout the day as trucks keep moving inside out.

news.title: Delhi HC expresses concern over newly built houses for EWS lying vacant
news.para: ​The high court took suo moto cognisance of the situation and said it was of the opinion that the process of completion of these houses ought to proceed expeditiously so that the slum dwellers in the city can be duly rehabilitated and can be offered these flats as per the policy framed.

news.title: Nagpur: Three-year jail to engineer-cum-builder for consumer forum contempt
news.para: While issuing a conviction warrant against Anil Potdukhe, who is also a planner, designer and an estimator, a bench comprising president Sanjay Patil and members Smita Chandekar and Avinash Prabhune directed him to pay Rs25,000 fine and Rs15,000 to the complainant towards the litigation cost.
